[2026-04-26]
CATEGORY: TEST_INFRASTRUCTURE
SERVICE: tests/contracts/
TASK: Extract Pydantic models to src/<service>/models.py; write contract tests.
SYMPTOM: First attempt at `pytest tests/contracts/` failed with ImportError: cannot
         import name 'Fact' from 'models' — it loaded src/channel_web/models.py
         instead of src/knowledge/models.py.
ROOT_CAUSE: All three services have a file named `models.py`. When pytest collects
            all contract test files, the first `sys.path.insert(..., "src/channel_web")`
            loads `models` into sys.modules. Subsequent files that insert
            `src/knowledge` at index 0 still get the cached channel_web version because
            Python never re-imports a key already in sys.modules.
PREVENTED_BY: When multiple services share a module filename, never use sys.path.insert
              for cross-service test imports. Use importlib.util.spec_from_file_location
              with a unique module name per service (e.g. "gateway.models",
              "knowledge.models", "channel_web.models"). This pattern is now documented
              in tests/CLAUDE.md.
SOLUTION: Replaced sys.path.insert approach with importlib.util.spec_from_file_location
          in all three contract test files. All 35 tests pass in a single invocation.

