              defines what "evidence present" means at the synthesis level, not the retrieval level.
              Do not add answer-text pattern matching to gateway without an approved spec in
              docs/specs/gateway.md. The answer relevance judge (gateway/TODO.md §Stage 3) is
              the right implementation vehicle once the spec exists.

[2026-04-27]
CATEGORY: ARCHITECTURE
SERVICE: src/gateway
TASK: Conversation policy gate design session
SYMPTOM: n/a — design session, no runtime failure
ROOT_CAUSE: n/a
INSIGHT: The classifier output (query_type) is not just a routing decision — it is a
  description of the expected answer shape. Both synthesis (downstream) and evaluation
  (feedback loop) depend on it. Without forwarding query_type to the knowledge service,
  synthesis uses a generic prompt regardless of question type. Without passing query_type
  to the answer relevance judge (Gate 4), the judge has no baseline: a high-level overview
  answer is correct for a broad question but wrong for a direct fact lookup.
  Dependency chain: classify(query_type) → synthesis prompt selection → answer shape expectation → judge criteria.
  All three must share the same classification or they will contradict each other.
PREVENTED_BY: Before implementing any answer quality judge, verify it receives query_type
  from the classifier and applies type-specific pass criteria. Before adding synthesis
  prompt variants to the knowledge service, ensure the gateway is forwarding query_type.
  See gateway/TODO.md §Stage 2 (intent tag forwarding) and §Stage 3 (answer relevance judge).

[2026-04-27]
CATEGORY: TEST_AUTHORING
SERVICE: tests/gateway
TASK: Gate 1 override — test for long-message no-override case
SYMPTOM: test_gate1_override_does_not_fire_for_long_message failed: classify.assert_called_once()
         failed even though the message was intended to be "too long" to trigger override.
ROOT_CAUSE: The override condition is `len(query.split()) < 15`. Test message
            "Actually I was asking about something that is definitely a school topic please check"
            has exactly 14 words — 14 < 15 is True, so the message triggered override despite
            also containing "check" as a trigger phrase. Off-by-one: 14 words is still
            "short" by the gate's definition.
PREVENTED_BY: When writing boundary tests for word-count thresholds, always print
              `len(msg.split())` to verify the test message actually crosses the boundary
              in the intended direction. Don't rely on prose length intuition.
