CATEGORY: DESIGN_SCOPE
SERVICE: src/gateway
TASK: Sprint item O — contextual classify
SYMPTOM: Proposed to use item O (contextual classify with history) to handle override intent
         ("look it up anyway") as well as affirmative follow-ups ("yes please"). Test
         confirmed the classifier correctly returns OOS for "look it up anyway" even with
         school-related history, because the message is a meta-command about pipeline
         behavior, not a school topic question.
ROOT_CAUSE: Conflated two different problems: (1) short affirmatives that inherit topic from
            context ("yes", "go ahead") — these ARE handled by history; (2) override intent
            ("look it up anyway") — this is never in_scope regardless of history because
            scope_gate.classify() asks "is this about school topics?", not "should we search?".
PREVENTED_BY: Before claiming a contextual classify change handles override intent, ask:
              "Would this message be in_scope if asked with no prior context?" If no,
              passing history into classify() will not help — it requires a separate classifier
              framed around pipeline intent, not topic scope.

