[2026-04-28]
CATEGORY: DEBUGGING
SERVICE: src/ingestion
TASK: Item R — Move build_index.py to src/ingestion/
SYMPTOM: Plan specified `Path(__file__).parents[2] / "knowledge"` to resolve src/knowledge/
         from src/ingestion/build_index.py. This resolves to <project_root>/knowledge/ which
         does not exist. The correct path is `parents[1] / "knowledge"` = src/knowledge/.
ROOT_CAUSE: Off-by-one in parents[] index. pathlib `parents[0]` = immediate parent directory.
            From src/ingestion/build_index.py: parents[0]=src/ingestion/, parents[1]=src/,
            parents[2]=<project_root>. Plan comment said "../../knowledge = src/knowledge"
            which is correct, but `..` from a file = `parents[0]`, so `../..` = `parents[1]`.
PREVENTED_BY: When writing sys.path.insert with Path.parents[], verify by counting manually:
              parents[0] = dir containing the file, parents[1] = one level up, etc. Then
              check: `python3 -c "from pathlib import Path; print(Path('/a/b/c.py').parents[1])"`.
              Never trust a plan's parents[] index without counting.

